  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dba \u0dc3\u0db3 \u0d85\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dc4\u0daf\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "China is trying to own the moon",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Bill Nelson, head of the US National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA), accuses China of trying to take possession of the moon under their military space program.",
        "The head of NASA made this accusation in an interview with Germany's Bild newspaper. \u201cChina is preparing to send astronauts to the moon through a military space program. Not on a scientific basis. I'm sure they want to own the moon. \"If they own the moon, we (America) or any other country will not be able to go to the moon again,\" explained the head of NASA.",
        "Regarding these accusations of the head of NASA, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the country has issued a statement on behalf of the Chinese government and protested. Zhao Lijiang, spokesman for the Chinese government's foreign ministry, said that the NASA chief made a baseless and irresponsible statement.",
        "China is currently building a small space station the size of the Earth's orbit. Part by part is sent up into the air and their assembly takes place in Lahilahi. The space station is scheduled to be completed this year, after which China will land on the moon.",
        "In 2024, the American NASA is going to start a series of lunar missions called 'Artemis'. The first time a woman was sent to the moon was under the 'Artemis' lunar mission. Accordingly, there will be a competition between the United States and China for the moon landing."
      ],
